    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "47c895ec_5c630041",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkHeifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 15
      },
      "lineNbr": 241,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-14T16:41:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oddly, if you know that your source data is opaque, it\u0027s faster to tell skcms that both the source and dest are unpremul. We treat opaque as a guarantee - we actually ignore the src alpha channel and overwrite it with 1.0 after reading, and if the dstAlpha is opaque, we overwrite alpha with 1.0 before writing.\n\nYes, this is confusing.",
      "revId": "25b9b40cd26481b9197ef396c7d4ed0e05c182a9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
